I have had tanks try to save me from adds.  I think people stopped doing this in my low 60s.  I pointed out to them that an Enchanter generated more aggro more rapidly than they can regain it, so let me channel through.   I still have time for Mezz (resist), Mezz (resist), Eldritch Rune, Tash, Mezz.<br>
<br>
Biggest issue I have had is clerics/healers that don't understand the tactical situation.  The worst message I can see on a resisted mezz is: &quot;Complete Heal incoming for Main Tank in 10 seconds&quot;.  Good clerics learn that CHeal is effective once Crowd Control is in effect.  Before that, fast heals are required.<br>
<br>
I have 2 alts a Cleric and an SK.<br>
<br>
After playing a Chanter so long, its hard to play a Cleric.  We watch different things at different points in battle.  Chanters prime role is a high intensity burst at beginning of a battle.  Clerics are required a lower intensity but constant role throughout a battle.  I generally use my fastest and smallest heal on enchanters (Ethereal Remedy, is the name I think).  I only use HoT on them when I am sure that they are no longer under attack.<br>
<br>
The SK is interesting as many enchanters try to mezz my pulls (and I generally pull with Snare but not always).  Its a bit more active during the battle due to positioning issues and aggro control.  Biggest issue that I see tanking is that most folks in their 50s (and my SK is 56) don't understand the riposte issue of mobs and position themselves properly.  In LDoN, generally I prefer to off tank single adds (i.e. we have 2 mobs).  I think that this is more effective than 1 at a time.  I see crowd control as a 3 or more on a pull issue.<br>
<br>
Playing the 3 classes has really deepened my understanding of group dynamics.  Between that and studying the capabilities of other classes, I think I am a much more effective enchanter.<br>
